341
00:38:38,343 --> 00:38:43,386
[SPEAKER_00]: And so adding the two projects together was well over a quarter of a million dollars.

342
00:38:43,826 --> 00:38:47,128
[SPEAKER_00]: So just a little clarification, you know, the threshold we're generally using is 250.

343
00:38:48,115 --> 00:38:51,517
[SPEAKER_00]: but that doesn't mean it's gonna be like exactly 250.

344
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:58,461
[SPEAKER_00]: We may present things underneath, if it seems in the spirit of attempting to present larger projects.

345
00:39:01,483 --> 00:39:02,543
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you, Madam Chair and staff.

346
00:39:02,563 --> 00:39:12,029
[SPEAKER_11]: So understanding, just a question for me, understanding that kind of sliding scale saying you may present things underneath, it would be binding the vote from the council.

347
00:39:12,089 --> 00:39:14,550
[SPEAKER_11]: It's not like just a courtesy.

348
00:39:14,610 --> 00:39:17,872
[SPEAKER_11]: This is actually, we either vote to appropriate or we don't,

349
00:39:21,238 --> 00:39:24,640
[SPEAKER_00]: I can't thank you, President for the question.

350
00:39:26,341 --> 00:39:28,342
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, the mayor's putting these forward.

351
00:39:28,382 --> 00:39:30,743
[SPEAKER_00]: I don't believe she has an obligation to do so.

352
00:39:31,423 --> 00:39:39,527
[SPEAKER_00]: Um, you know, obviously, the mayor would be looking for the city council support and the positive feedback and the

353
00:39:40,178 --> 00:39:46,882
[SPEAKER_00]: essentially the majority of the City Council, if not unanimous approval of the City Council on these, that would be very positive.

354
00:39:47,422 --> 00:39:55,447
[SPEAKER_00]: Obviously, you know, in the end, if the decision lies with the Mayor, I can't speak to it if she feels that one of the projects is a major priority.

355
00:39:56,027 --> 00:40:00,950
[SPEAKER_00]: My understanding of why the City Council is looking to have these projects

356
00:40:01,532 --> 00:40:08,677
[SPEAKER_00]: physically presented before them is to present ideas on how the projects may improve before they get out the door.

357
00:40:08,717 --> 00:40:12,640
[SPEAKER_00]: At least that was one member's, Vice President Baird's comments.

358
00:40:13,461 --> 00:40:23,829
[SPEAKER_00]: In the end, the reality is the mayor was looking initially to pass these projects before the council to get any feedback.

359
00:40:24,189 --> 00:40:27,792
[SPEAKER_00]: So our values align on that, it's just a matter of

360
00:40:28,363 --> 00:40:30,443
[SPEAKER_00]: you know, do you have any suggestions or thoughts?

361
00:40:30,743 --> 00:40:33,864
[SPEAKER_00]: Do you have any feedback on this that we need to take into consideration?

362
00:40:34,324 --> 00:40:45,006
[SPEAKER_00]: I can't commit to anything much beyond that, but as we are discussing here today, we appreciate the council's comments and feedback, and we'll definitely take them into consideration.

363
00:40:46,067 --> 00:40:51,548
[SPEAKER_00]: If you want a more, I'd have to speak with the mayor for a more firm answer.

364
00:40:51,568 --> 00:40:54,088
[SPEAKER_11]: Okay, thank you, Madam Chief of Staff.

365
00:40:56,409 --> 00:40:58,129
[SPEAKER_11]: Any further discussion from the council at this point?

